Seen while investigating `-Wunused-but-set-variable`. OS_Unix has a static function `has_data()` while basically always returns false: https://github.com/godotengine/godot/blob/9073dc9/drivers/unix/os_unix.cpp#L187-L198

``` c++
static int has_data(FILE* p_fd, int timeout_usec = 0) {

    fd_set readset;
    int fd = fileno(p_fd);
    FD_ZERO(&readset);
    FD_SET(fd, &readset);
    timeval time;
    time.tv_sec = 0;
    time.tv_usec = timeout_usec;
    int res = 0;//select(fd + 1, &readset, NULL, NULL, &time);
    return res > 0;
};
```

Which means that the code chunk where it's used is also never triggered: https://github.com/godotengine/godot/blob/9073dc9/drivers/unix/os_unix.cpp#L211-L223

So the function should either be fixed, or dropped together with the `while (has_data(stdin)) {}` loop in `OS_Unix::get_stdin_string()`.
